<L>__{interior union station ticket booth night}
<A>__{gordon northcott makes his way to the ticket booth.}
<C>__{gordon}
<D>__{i'd like a ticket to canada. alberta or vancouver, whatever's leaving tonight.}
<C>__{ticket vender}
<D>__{don't have anything going that far tonight. best i can do is put you on a train for seattle. from there you can transfer to one of the locals or drive across the border.}
<C>__{gordon}
<D>__{that'll be fine.}
<C>__{ticket vender}
<D>__{round trip?}
<C>__{gordon}
<D>__{one way.}
<A>__{the vender moves away to pull the ticket. gordon glances at a cop heading his way. stiffens. the cop continues past him. gordon relaxes as the vender slides the ticket across.}
<C>__{ticket vender}
<D>__{that'll be fifteen dollars.}
<A>__{gordon pays for the ticket and heads toward the boarding gates.}
